Date Published:2019-06-24 00:00:00      
The ill-fated lost their lives and 67 others got injured when five bogies of Dhaka-bound Upaban Express train-- coming from Sylhet-- veered off the tracks Five people met their deaths in a train accident in around 11:40pm on Sunday. The ill-fated lost their lives and 67 others got injured when five bogies of Dhaka-bound Upaban Express train-- coming from Sylhet-- veered off the tracks after a culvert over the Barochhara Canal broke down. Two of the bogies fell into the canal and one of them overturned, while the other bogies remained tilted.
